  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Contract Administrator",
  "description": "<h3><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>Prepare, review, and administer main contracts and subcontracts for fire protection projects.</li>\n  <li>Support tendering and cost estimation activities, including quantity take-off and preparation of BOQs.</li>\n  <li>Evaluate and process progress claims, variation orders, and final accounts for clients and subcontractors.</li>\n  <li>Ensure proper contract documentation, correspondences, and filing in accordance with company procedures.</li>\n  <li>Coordinate with project managers, site teams, and clients to resolve contractual or commercial issues.</li>\n  <li>Monitor project cost performance, prepare cost reports, and assist in budget control.</li>\n  <li>Prepare claims, extension of time (EOT) submissions, and assist in contract negotiations when required.</li>\n  <li>Ensure all contractual obligations, statutory requirements, and company policies are complied with.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><strong>Requirements</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>Diploma or Degree in <strong>Quantity Surveying</strong>, <strong>Building</strong>, <strong>Construction Management</strong>, or related discipline.</li>\n  <li>Minimum <strong>2–5 years</strong> of relevant experience in <strong>construction contracts administration</strong>, preferably in <strong>fire protection</strong>, <strong>M&amp;E</strong>, or <strong>ACMV</strong> works.</li>\n  <li>Familiar with standard forms of contracts (e.g. PSSCOC, SIA, or FIDIC).</li>\n  <li>Proficient in Microsoft Office and QS-related software (e.g. CostX, Cubicost).</li>\n  <li>Strong analytical, communication, and negotiation skills.</li>\n  <li>Detail-oriented and able to handle multiple tasks within tight deadlines.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><strong>Preferred Attributes</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>Experience working with <strong>fire protection systems</strong> such as sprinklers, hose reels, and suppression systems.</li>\n  <li>Knowledge of <strong>local authority requirements</strong> (e.g. SCDF regulations) will be an added advantage.</li>\n  <li>Team player with a positive attitude and willingness to take initiative.</li>\n</ul>",
